    <p>{`Multimodal distributions where the modes barely overlap typically pose difficulties to MCMC algorithms. This is because exploring them fully requires entering and passing through a region of low probability density which, by the very nature of MCMC, is a rare event.`}</p>
    <p>{`Lets see how many samples HMC requires to achieve mixing, i.e. to jump from whichever mode we sample first to the other. Once both modes are covered with roughly equal numbers of samples, we can use the generated Markov chain `}<span parentName="p" {...{
        "className": "katex"
      }}><span parentName="span" {...{
